<subSubSection id="BC4386ABD71F489EA9055056D5194258" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" type="notes">
<paragraph id="A46937EB945A7E78E8222DB2E0853954" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD5EF294A6ACBE6E2BA8A0986C21A054" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">
It is presently unclear, whether this poorly described and illustrated taxon that is only known from a single collection is simply 
<taxonomicName id="254A7A41FE78648ABC1C467D61249069" authorityName="Jaklitsch &amp; Voglmayr" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis marginalis subsp. europaea" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="marginalis" subSpecies="europaea">Melanconis marginalis subsp. europaea</taxonomicName>
or merits a subspecies name of its own. First, the host given by the authors, 
<taxonomicName id="99BE7504950FACDE0FC49D90B5C72B69" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Alnus cordata" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cordata">
<emphasis id="674C101EB4DD57768C9EFAFD45E20709" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Alnus cordata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, naturally occurs in southern Italy and Corsica and, thus, may be correct only if planted in the collection area, which is not given by the authors. Secondly, the ascospores are in the range of other subspecies and appendages are neither mentioned nor illustrated, although a few are visible in their ascus images. Apparently, ascospores were mounted in KOH, where appendages are invisible. Thirdly, they describe the asexual morph from culture and include only a poor image of conidia without giving any measurements. Last but not least, only LSU, ITS and 
<emphasis id="F3821112732268808C5D46B1D97A1951" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">rpb2</emphasis>
are available, which are insufficient to reliably resolve its true phylogenetic position. In addition, instead of comparing their taxon with 
<taxonomicName id="A1CCD9AEE9337188D5989BFF62364E91" genus="M." lsidName="M. marginalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis id="D0EA27817F33026E45D9C77972DD608E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, they compare it with 
<taxonomicName id="E456D65FEE596EA5EC71F9F37781FA40" genus="M." lsidName="M. alnicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alnicola">
<emphasis id="572D2062583B5A5AF129FA867B7D9A51" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alnicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="89A966B5D74EAB09B0E8564B07490598" author="Jaap, O" journalOrPublisher="Annales Mycologici" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="97 - 124" refId="B14" refString="Jaap, O, 1917. Weitere Beitraege zur Pilzflora der Schweiz. Annales Mycologici 15: 97 - 124" title="Weitere Beitraege zur Pilzflora der Schweiz." volume="15" year="1917">Jaap 1917</bibRefCitation>
), which is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="189BA3712A5D9244DB208439672D29BE" authorityName="Voglmayr &amp; Jaklitsch" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Berk. &amp; Broome" class="Sordariomycetes" genus="Alnecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Alnecium auctum" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="auctum">
<emphasis id="617338BFF7DADF2F11ABE5E6EF6C4F63" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Alnecium auctum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
